1.Title of the Project
Development of n Interactive Business Intelligence Dashboard Integrating Machine Learning Outputs.
2.Problem Statement in details (200 words)
Design and implement a comprehensive Power BI dashboard that consolidates processed datasets along with machine learning model predictions to enable data-driven decision-making. The system must integrate data from multiple sources, including cleaned historical datasets and predictive outputs such as classification results, regression forecasts, or clustering insights. The dashboard should transform this combined data into meaningful, interactive visualizations such as bar charts, line graphs, heatmaps, and drill-down reports.
A key requirement is the inclusion of dynamic KPI tracking, where metrics such as accuracy, sales trends, customer segmentation performance, or operational efficiency are continuously monitored. Users should be able to filter, slice, and explore data in real time to uncover patterns and anomalies. The dashboard must also support comparative analysis, allowing stakeholders to evaluate actual outcomes against predicted results.
Additionally, the system should provide decision-support insights by highlighting trends, forecasting future outcomes, and identifying key drivers influencing performance. Proper data modeling, relationship management, and DAX calculations should be used to ensure accuracy and responsiveness. The final dashboard must be user-friendly, visually intuitive, and optimized for performance, enabling stakeholders to make informed strategic decisions efficiently based on both historical and predictive analytics.


3.Methodology (details, may include block diagram)
The project follows a structured data engineering and analytics pipeline:
Data Collection: Gather raw datasets from sources such as CSV files, databases, or APIs. 
Data Preprocessing: Clean missing values, remove duplicates, normalize formats, and handle outliers. 
Data Transformation: Convert data into structured format suitable for analysis (feature engineering, encoding categorical variables). 
Machine Learning Integration: Train a model (e.g., regression/classification) using historical data and generate predictions. 
Data Storage: Store processed data and predictions in a structured format (e.g., SQL database or Excel). 
Power BI Integration: Import datasets into Power BI and establish relationships. 
Visualization & KPI Creation: Build dashboards using charts, filters, and DAX-based KPIs. 
Block Flow (Textual Diagram):
Raw Data → Data Cleaning → Data Transformation → ML Model → Predictions → Data Storage → Power BI → Dashboard & Insights

4.Algorithms/steps in details 
·  Load dataset 
·  Perform data cleaning (null handling, duplicate removal) 
·  Conduct exploratory data analysis (EDA) 
·  Select relevant features 
·  Split dataset into training and testing sets 
·  Train machine learning model (e.g., Linear Regression / Decision Tree) 
·  Evaluate model using metrics (accuracy, RMSE, etc.) 
·  Generate predictions 
·  Export predictions with dataset 
·  Import data into Power BI 
·  Create relationships between tables 
·  Design visualizations (charts, slicers, KPIs) 
·  Publish dashboard

5. Program
	BEGIN
  LOAD dataset
  CLEAN dataset:
      HANDLE missing values
      REMOVE duplicates
  TRANSFORM data:
      ENCODE categorical variables
      NORMALIZE numerical values

  SPLIT data into training and testing sets

  TRAIN model using training data
  PREDICT results using testing data

  EVALUATE model performance

  SAVE processed data + predictions to file

  IMPORT data into Power BI
  CREATE relationships between tables
  BUILD visualizations and KPIs

END

6.Result 
·  Successfully developed an interactive Power BI dashboard. 
·  Integrated machine learning predictions with processed datasets. 
·  Visualizations display trends, comparisons, and forecasts. 
·  KPIs provide real-time performance tracking. 
·  Dashboard supports filtering and drill-down analysis.

7 Discussion/Observation
·  Data quality significantly affects model accuracy and visualization reliability. 
·  Machine learning predictions enhance analytical depth compared to static dashboards. 
·  Interactive filters improve usability and decision-making efficiency. 
·  Performance optimization is necessary when handling large datasets. 
·  Some prediction errors observed due to limited or noisy data.

8 Conclusion
The project demonstrates the integration of data engineering, machine learning, and business intelligence tools to create a decision-support system. The Power BI dashboard effectively transforms raw and predictive data into actionable insights. This approach improves analytical capabilities and supports informed decision-making through interactive and real-time visualization.

